In this statement, issued on October 25, 2019, President Trump and First Lady Melania send their best wishes to those celebrating Diwali, the Festival of Lights. They acknowledge the significance of this sacred period for Hindus, Jains, Sikhs, and Buddhists, and highlight its message of victory of light over darkness, good over evil, and knowledge over ignorance. The President emphasizes the importance of religious liberty and states that his administration will continue to defend the rights of people of all faiths to worship according to their beliefs. The statement concludes with a prayer for love, joy, and eternal peace during this year's Diwali observance.